Package: metamanager
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, jq, inotify-tools, libimage-exiftool-perl, libjpeg-turbo-progs, optipng, webp, ffmpeg
Recommends: wp-cli
Description: OS-level daemons for Metamanager WordPress plugin
 Metamanager provides lossless image compression (jpegtran, optipng, cwebp),
 bidirectional EXIF/IPTC/XMP metadata sync via ExifTool, and video/audio
 metadata handling via ffmpeg — all driven by OS-level daemons so WordPress
 or wp-cron are not on the hot path.
 .
 This package ships the compress and metadata daemons, their systemd units,
 and the installer script. The postinst runs metamanager-install.sh --no-deps,
 which auto-detects the WordPress content directory, patches the daemon
 scripts and systemd units with the detected path, enables and starts both
 daemons, and installs the plugin from GitHub if available.
